<br>
Dwarves have low agi, mine is base 71.  I had recently replaced my sentry choker 9ac 4agi etc stats with a Polished Mithral Torque 7ac 13wis 13int.  After you all told me how _important_ wisdom is to a paladin, i did this without thinking.  Unfortunately that was my last piece of agi gear.  Recently i noticed when i equiped my trueheart shield (20ac 5str 5wis 5agi) and my wurmy i got about ~80ac out of the deal.  So i started playing around with my gear.  Low and behold, replacing torque with the choker i gain not 3 or 4 ac, but 42ac... i am now at 75agi. When i equip my shield and wurmy.. i am up now only 40 more ac (where it should be).<br>
<br>
So i determined that when you pass 75 agi, you get an ac bonus.  However, with my low agi i cant experiment into the higher ranges to find ou where other caps may lie.  If you care to play around with it, let me know what you find out<br>
<br>
-Ferok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uazzigothghul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzigoth Ghul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/26/01 11:11:19 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agi-ac Bonuses</span><hr size=1> 75 is the important number to get.<br>
